                <h1>The Psychology of Oppression in The Yellow Wallpaper</h1>
                <p>In "The Yellow Wallpaper," Charlotte Perkins Gilman explores the theme of oppression, particularly the societal constraints placed on women in the 19th century. The protagonist's descent into madness mirrors her struggle against the stifling norms of her domestic life, revealing how mental health can be affected by oppressive environments.</p>
